Author: plinkplonk
Title: Reminder: The DARPA Car Race is on
Content:
The webcast doesn't seem to be working ( :-(( ), but I am trying to follow the action from various blog posts and it seems that 3 (of 11) robots have already dropped out. The Stanford vehicle (Junior) has completed phase (one of 3).

I envy people who can follow the race from the race course - this years challenge is Urban Navigation, following traffic rules etc.

I am vicariously following the race from Bangalore by reading blogs on the race (here is the latest post I could find http://crave.cnet.com/8301-1_105-9810371-1.html). 

 I thought others might be interested and hence the reminder. please vote down if inappropriate.

Author: nostrademons
Content: Check out article 3 in the issue. He writes a program to solve a simple puzzle game entirely in the Haskell type system. Including building up notions for booleans, lists, functions, and map/filter/comprehensions from scratch.
